"'''A Credit for Your Thoughts'''" is a short story by [[Tish Eggleston Pahl]] and [[Chris Cassidy]]. It was originally published in [[Star Wars Gamer 2|''Star Wars Gamer'' 2]] in [[2001]].

==Plot summary==
[[Fenig Nabon]] enters the [[Black Dust Tavern]], where she gets a drink from her [[Bartender/Legends|bartender]] and friend [[Karl Mathieu Ancher]] in memory of her late foster father [[Jett Nabon|Jett]], before approaching her client [[Talon Karrde]] to discuss business. After she was paid, Talon discussed the aftermath of [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba's]] [[Battle of the Great Pit of Carkoon|death]] and the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|destruction]] of the [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]]. Talon then gave her a [[Datacard/Legends|data disk]] as he was planning to establish a base to form an organization of smugglers. He then noticed [[Ghitsa Dogder]], a [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]-born [[Con artist/Legends|con artist]] who was currently pushing a scam with [[Aves]] and holding a [[retinal disguiser]]. Wanting her to stop cheating on Talon's people, Fenig offered Talon to get her off Aves. Aves was starting to not take the bait when she arrived and told him that Talon wants him.

An arm belonging to a [[Gran/Legends|Gran]] [[Gecee]] arrived, angered at Dogder for selling him a code that caused a patrol in [[Kuat/Legends|Kuat]] to try to apprehend him. She remarked on his foolishness to take the code at such a cheap price. Just as Gecee was about to swing a strike at Dogder, Fenig grabbed a bottle and smashed it on Gecee, causing a bar fight with over 50 patrons, including her friends [[Hrdinah]] and [[Radek]], which was stopped by Karl with a [[Calli-Merc blaster pistol]].

After Fenig helped Karl clean up the mess, she found herself in a tense walk for her ship the ''[[Star Lady]]'' in the [[Soco-Jarel Spaceport]] while keeping an eye out for Gecee, only to find Ghitsa inside her ship. After a tense moment the two sat down to matters related to the bar fight and to the prospects of recent events in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]], to Fenn wanting to settle down on a vacation property. Just as Dogder started to leave the ''Star Lady'', Fenig soon caught up to her to find Gecee armed with a heavy blaster. After convincing her to drop her blaster and tried to drag Dogder with him only for her to feign falling over with her high heels and grabbed his ear, immobilizing him. But his gang then radioed for an update and both realized that company was coming, so Fenig picked up her blaster as Gecee's [[Swoop/Legends|swoop]] [[Swoop gang/Legends|gang]] arrived and started shooting. Fenig got the ship to life from the spaceport.

With the help of [[Shind]] giving her the clearance for takeoff and giving Gecee a customs inspection notice, the two cleared the distance from their pursuers and then brokered a deal between them as the ''Star Lady'' jumped to [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]].

